results.name: Largest nonprime proper divisor of n (with a(1)=1).
comment: a(m)*a(n) <= a(m*n); a(m)*a(n) = a(m*n) iff m and n are prime or = 1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 11 2008
link: R. Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
program: (PARI) { for (n=1, 1000, if (n==1, a=1, d=divisors(n); m=length(d); until (!isprime(a), m--; a=d[m])); write("b063928.txt", n, " ", a) ) } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Sep 02 2009
xref: a(n)=1 if n is 1, prime (A000040), or the product of two primes (A001358), i.e., if n is in A037143, otherwise, with n in A033942, a(n)=A032742(n). Cf. A006530.
results.author: _Henry Bottomley_, Aug 15 2001
